  <summary>6/8/2004--Introduced.
Children's Sleepwear Safety Act of 2004 - Requires the Consumer Product Safety Commission to amend its standards under the Flammable Fabrics Act to revoke amendments relaxing flammability standards for children's sleepwear that the Commission issued on September 9, 1996.</summary>
